The paper deals with distance labeling in graphs, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of distance labeling also has connections to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for distance labeling, which could be of interest to researchers in network engineering (cs.NE) and social networks (cs.SI).
